// return all records
GET /person

// return a specific record
GET /person/{id}

// create a new record
POST /person

// update an existing record
PUT /person/{id}

// delete an existing record
DELETE /person/{id}

To run PHP server 
php -S 127.0.0.1:8000 -t public


DB_HOST=localhost
DB_PORT=3306
DB_DATABASE=api_example
DB_USERNAME=api_user
DB_PASSWORD=api_password


I removed from FE http://127.0.0.1:8000/user?action=register
To get register we did 
$action = $_GET['action'] ?? '';  // Fetch action from query params

Now we are accessing this API by http://127.0.0.1:8000/user/register

You will possiby need to run these two commands
composer require vlucas/phpdotenv
composer require firebase/php-jwt

There will be a SQL script to initialize the database and to create tables.
-> Check db_ini.sql
